          "front": "What causes Peripheral Arterial Disease (P.A.D.) ?",
          "back": "The most common cause of P.A.D. is atherosclerosis, a buildup of plaque in the arteries. Over time, plaque can harden and narrow the arteries. This limits the flow of oxygen-rich blood to your organs and other parts of your body."
